  "prompt": "What are group tasks given in MBA admission test especially the IITs?",
  "response": "In MBA admission tests like those conducted by IITs (through CAT or their specific entrance exams), group tasks typically include:\n\n1. Group Discussion (GD)\n- Current affairs topics\n- Management/business-related issues\n- Social and economic problems\n- Abstract conceptual themes\n\n2. Group Problem-Solving Tasks\n- Case study analysis\n- Solving business scenarios\n- Strategy development exercises\n- Team decision-making challenges\n\n3. Common Group Tasks\n- Collaborative brainstorming\n- Consensus building\n- Presenting group solutions\n- Analyzing complex business situations\n\n4. Specific Assessment Parameters\n- Communication skills\n- Leadership potential\n- Team collaboration\n- Critical thinking\n- Logical reasoning\n- Presentation abilities\n- Interpersonal skills\n\n5. Typical Group Task Formats\n- Panel discussions\n- Role-playing scenarios\n- Group presentations\n- Simulation exercises\n- Problem-solving assignments\n\n6. Evaluation Criteria\n- Quality of arguments\n- Listening skills\n- Respectful communication\n- Constructive contribution\n- Analytical approach\n- Innovative thinking\n\nThese group tasks assess candidates' potential management and leadership capabilities beyond academic qualifications.",
